7. Explain the ”60-30-10 Rule” regarding color balance on a website.
The 60-30-10 Rule is a guideline for color proportioning on a website to create a balanced, visually appealing design:

60% - Dominant Color:
Usually the background color or main theme.
ets the overall tone of the site.

30% - Secondary Color:
Supports the dominant color and is used for secondary elements like sidebars, menus, or highlights.

10% - Accent Color:
Used sparingly to draw attention to important elements like buttons, links, or CTAs.

Example:
Website background (dominant) → White → 60%
Menu, banners, sidebar (secondary) → Light Gray → 30%
Buttons, links, highlights (accent) → Red → 10%

Benefits:
Maintains visual harmony
Guides users’ focus naturally
Avoids color clutter

